@startuml logical-architecture-its
!include ../_shared/its-uml-style.puml

title Issue Tracking System - Logical Architecture Overview

top to bottom direction

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 48
skinparam ranksep 48
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam rectangle {
  FontSize 13
  BorderColor #37474F
  FontColor #263238
}

rectangle "Presentation Layer\n--\nJavaFXApp and SwingApp entry points\nBoth UI toolkits reuse the same application boundary" as PRES <<presentation>> #E3F2FD

rectangle "Application Bootstrap\n--\nMain\nApplicationContext\nApplicationBootstrap" as BOOT <<bootstrap>> #E8F5E9

rectangle "Controller Layer\n--\nUse-case entry points\nCurrent-user boundary" as CTRL <<controller>> #FFF8E1

rectangle "Service / Policy Layer\n--\nUse-case orchestration\nPermissionPolicy\nWorkflow / recommendation policies" as SERVICE <<service>> #FFF3E0

rectangle "Domain Model\n--\nUser / Project / ProjectMember\nIssue / Comment / IssueHistory / IssueDependency\nRole / Status / Priority / Action values" as DOMAIN <<domain>> #F1F8E9

rectangle "Application Ports\n--\nRepository interfaces\nClock / PasswordHashing\nCurrentUserSession / CommentIdProvider" as PORTS <<port>> #E0F2F1

rectangle "Infrastructure Adapters\n--\nJDBC repositories\nPasswordHasher / SessionStore / SystemClock\nCommentIdGenerator" as INFRA <<adapter>> #F3E5F5

database "Oracle Database" as DB #ECEFF1

PRES -down-> BOOT : starts application
BOOT -down-> CTRL : wires controllers
BOOT -down-> SERVICE : wires services and policies
BOOT -down-> INFRA : creates adapters
CTRL -down-> SERVICE : delegates use cases
SERVICE -down-> DOMAIN : applies domain behavior
SERVICE -down-> PORTS : uses ports
INFRA -up-> PORTS : implements ports
INFRA -down-> DB : persists data
@enduml
